	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started a Gnome cleric recently...as my third character "Quignosh" on the Vazselle server...this was before I read all these negative posts about Gnomish clerics. I have had a blast with him!! I have twinked a little...got a ranger in Unrest who passes on some ringmail he finds on ghouls, but I have had a blast! In part because so many people have never seen a gnomish cleric and want to ask me about it. Anyway I have to agree with everyone who says play what you like...this is a role playing game. In life not everyone is perfect for the role they choose but they do the bast they can. Same thing in EQ...make up for your shortcomings in your chosen class by roleplaying...those of you who think this game is all about "leveling" miss a lot of fun of exploring and discovering. If anyone is ever on Vazselle....look up ol' Quignosh..9th(so far) level cleric...who is having a blast as a cleric and doent seem to realize he isnt supposed to be any good at it!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
